As part of the IBM Data Analyst Professional Certificate, I completed a hands-on project on creating interactive dashboards using Excel.

This exercise helped me apply concepts such as:
📌 Building dashboard layouts for decision-makers
📌 Creating PivotTables and PivotCharts
📌 Using slicers for interactive filtering
📌 Presenting multiple KPIs in a single view
📌 Transforming raw data into actionable insights

The biggest takeaway was that a dashboard isn't just a collection of charts—it's a decision-making tool that enables stakeholders to identify trends and make informed business decisions quickly.
